  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use monads and comonads when you can:\nStart from a category (or a poset viewed as a thin category). Identify an endofunctor T : C -\u0026gt; C that \u0026ldquo;wraps\u0026rdquo; or \u0026ldquo;annotates\u0026rdquo; objects. Ask whether the wrapping is coherent: can it be applied once, twice, or unwrapped, in ways that compose consistently? ¶Definitions A monad on a category C is a triple (T, eta, mu) where:\n",
